{"title_page": "Alexander, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken", "text_new": "{{ infobox nobility\n| name         = Alexander of Zweibr\u00fccken\n| image        = \n| caption      = \n| noble family = [[House of Wittelsbach]]\n| father       = [[Louis I, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken]]\n| mother       = Johanna of Cro\u00ff\n| spouse       = Margarete of Hohenlohe-Neuenstein\n| issue        = {{plainlist|\n* [[Louis II, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken|Louis II]]\n* [[Rupert, Count Palatine of Veldenz|Rupert]]\n}}\n| issue-link   = #Family and children\n| birth_date   = {{birth_date|1462|11|26|df=yes}}\n| birth_place  = \n| death_date   = {{death date and age|1514|10|21|1462|11|26|df=yes}}\n| death_place  = [[Zweibr\u00fccken]]\n}}\n'''Alexander of Zweibr\u00fccken''' ({{lang-de|Pfalzgraf Alexander von Zweibr\u00fccken \"der Hinkende\"}}) (26 November 1462 \u2013 21 October 1514) was [[Count palatine|Count Palatine]] and Duke of [[Zweibr\u00fccken]] and of [[Veldenz]] in 1489\u20131514.\n\nHe was the son of [[Louis I, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken]] and his wife [[Johanna of Cro\u00ff]]. Alexander promised to establish a church after the successful return from a crusade, and it was kept in 1489 with the building of the Alexanderskirche in [[Zweibr\u00fccken]].\n\n==Family and children==\nHe was married in 1499 in Zweibr\u00fccken to Countess [[Margarete of Hohenlohe-Neuenstein]], daughter of Count [[Kraft VI of Hohenlohe]] and [[Helene of W\u00fcrttemberg]]. They had the following children:\n# Johanna (1499\u20131537), a nun in [[Trier]].\n# [[Louis II, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken|Louis II]] (1502\u20131532).\n# George (1503\u20131537), a canon in Trier, [[Strassburg]] and [[Cologne]].\n# Margarete (1509\u20131522), a nun at Marienberg bei Boppard.\n# [[Rupert, Count Palatine of Veldenz|Rupert]] (1506\u20131544).\n# Katharina (1510\u20131542), married before 1 February 1541 to Count [[Otto IV of Rietberg]].\n\n== Ancestors ==\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center\n|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;\n|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;\n|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;\n|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;\n|boxstyle_5=background-color: #9fe;\n| 1= 1. '''Alexander, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken'''\n| 2= 2. [[Louis I, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken]]\n| 3= 3. Johanna of Cro\u00ff\n| 4= 4. [[Stephen, Count Palatine of Simmern-Zweibr\u00fccken]]\n| 5= 5. [[Anna of Veldenz, Countess Palatine of Simmern-Zweibr\u00fccken|Anna of Veldenz]]\n| 6= 6. [[Antoine I de Cro\u00ff]]\n| 7= 7. Margaret of Lorraine-Vaud\u00e9mont\n| 8= 8. [[Rupert of Germany]]\n| 9= 9. [[Elisabeth of Nuremberg]]\n| 10= 10. Frederick III of Veldenz\n| 11= 11. Margaret of Nassau-Saarbr\u00fccken\n| 12= 12. [[Jean I de Cro\u00ff]]\n| 13= 13. Marie de Craon\n| 14= 14. [[Antoine, Count of Vaud\u00e9mont]]\n| 15= 15. [[Marie, Countess of Harcourt]]\n| 16= 16. [[Rupert II, Elector Palatine]]\n| 17= 17. [[Beatrice of Sicily (1326\u20131365)]]\n| 18= 18. [[Frederick V, Burgrave of Nuremberg]]\n| 19= 19. [[Elisabeth of Meissen]]\n| 20= 20. Henry III of Veldenz\n| 21= 21. [[Loretta of Sponheim|Loretta of Sponheim-Starkenburg]]\n| 22= 22. [[John I, Count of Nassau-Weilburg]]\n| 23= 23. Joanna of Saarbr\u00fccken\n| 24= 24. Guillaume de Cro\u00ff\n| 25= 25. Isabeau de Renty\n| 26= 26. John I of Craon\n| 27= 27. Marie de Ch\u00e2tillon-sur-Marne\n| 28= 28. [[Frederick of Lorraine, Count of Vaud\u00e9mont]]\n| 29= 29. [[Margaret of Joinville]]\n| 30= 30. [[John VII of Harcourt]]\n| 31= 31. [[Marie of Alen\u00e7on]]\n}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-hou|[[House of Wittelsbach]]|26 November|1462|21 October|1514}}\n{{s-bef|rows=2|before=[[Louis I, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken|Louis I]]}}\n{{s-ttl|rows=1|years=1489&ndash;1514|title=[[Duke and Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken|Duke of Zweibr\u00fccken]]}}\n{{s-aft|rows=1|after=[[Louis II, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken|Louis II]]}}\n{{s-ttl|rows=1|title=[[Count of Veldenz]]|years=1489&ndash;1514}}\n{{s-aft|rows=1|after=[[Rupert, Count Palatine of Veldenz|Rupert]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20071128060836/http://www.gen.heinz-wember.de/wittelsbacher/Alexander1462.htm Die Genealogie der Wittelsbacher ]\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2012}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alexander, Count Palatine Of Zweibrucken}}\n[[Category:1462 births|Wittelsbach, Alexander of Pfalz-Zweibrucken]]\n[[Category:1514 deaths|Wittelsbach, Alexander of Pfalz-Zweibrucken]]\n[[Category:House of Palatinate-Zweibr\u00fccken]]\n[[Category:Christians of the Crusades|Wittelsbach, Alexander of Pfalz-Zweibrucken]]\n[[Category:Counts Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken]]\n", "text_old": "{{ infobox nobility\n| name = Alexander of Zweibr\u00fccken\n| image = \n| caption = \n| noble family = [[House of Wittelsbach]]\n| father = [[Louis I, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken]]\n| mother = Johanna of Cro\u00ff\n| spouse = Margarete of Hohenlohe-Neuenstein\n| issue = {{plainlist|\n* [[Louis II, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken|Louis II]]\n* [[Rupert, Count Palatine of Veldenz|Rupert]]\n}}\n| issue-link = #Family and children\n| birth_date = {{birth_date|1462|11|26|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = \n| death_date = {{death date and age|1514|10|21|1462|11|26|df=yes}}\n| death_place = [[Zweibr\u00fccken]]\n}}\n'''Alexander of Zweibr\u00fccken''' ({{lang-de|Pfalzgraf Alexander von Zweibr\u00fccken \"der Hinkende\"}}) (26 November 1462 \u2013 21 October 1514) was [[Count palatine|Count Palatine]] and Duke of [[Zweibr\u00fccken]] and of [[Veldenz]] in 1489\u20131514.\n\nHe was the son of [[Louis I, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken]] and his wife [[Johanna of Cro\u00ff]]. Alexander promised to establish a church after the successful return from a crusade, and it was kept in 1489 with the building of the Alexanderskirche in [[Zweibr\u00fccken]].\n\n==Family and children==\nHe was married in 1499 in Zweibr\u00fccken to Countess [[Margarete of Hohenlohe-Neuenstein]], daughter of Count [[Kraft VI of Hohenlohe]] and [[Helene of W\u00fcrttemberg]]. They had the following children:\n# Johanna (1499\u20131537), a nun in [[Trier]].\n# [[Louis II, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken|Louis II]] (1502\u20131532).\n# George (1503\u20131537), a canon in Trier, [[Strassburg]] and [[Cologne]].\n# Margarete (1509\u20131522), a nun at Marienberg bei Boppard.\n# [[Rupert, Count Palatine of Veldenz|Rupert]] (1506\u20131544).\n# Katharina (1510\u20131542), married before 1 February 1541 to Count [[Otto IV of Rietberg]].\n\n== Ancestors ==\n{{ahnentafel\n|collapsed=yes |align=center\n|boxstyle_1=background-color: #fcc;\n|boxstyle_2=background-color: #fb9;\n|boxstyle_3=background-color: #ffc;\n|boxstyle_4=background-color: #bfc;\n|boxstyle_5=background-color: #9fe;\n| 1= 1. '''Alexander, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken'''\n| 2= 2. [[Louis I, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken]]\n| 3= 3. Johanna of Cro\u00ff\n| 4= 4. [[Stephen, Count Palatine of Simmern-Zweibr\u00fccken]]\n| 5= 5. [[Anna of Veldenz, Countess Palatine of Simmern-Zweibr\u00fccken|Anna of Veldenz]]\n| 6= 6. [[Antoine I de Cro\u00ff]]\n| 7= 7. Margaret of Lorraine-Vaud\u00e9mont\n| 8= 8. [[Rupert of Germany]]\n| 9= 9. [[Elisabeth of Nuremberg]]\n| 10= 10. Frederick III of Veldenz\n| 11= 11. Margaret of Nassau-Saarbr\u00fccken\n| 12= 12. [[Jean I de Cro\u00ff]]\n| 13= 13. Marie de Craon\n| 14= 14. [[Antoine, Count of Vaud\u00e9mont]]\n| 15= 15. [[Marie, Countess of Harcourt]]\n| 16= 16. [[Rupert II, Elector Palatine]]\n| 17= 17. [[Beatrice of Sicily (1326\u20131365)]]\n| 18= 18. [[Frederick V, Burgrave of Nuremberg]]\n| 19= 19. [[Elisabeth of Meissen]]\n| 20= 20. Henry III of Veldenz\n| 21= 21. [[Loretta of Sponheim|Loretta of Sponheim-Starkenburg]]\n| 22= 22. [[John I, Count of Nassau-Weilburg]]\n| 23= 23. Joanna of Saarbr\u00fccken\n| 24= 24. Guillaume de Cro\u00ff\n| 25= 25. Isabeau de Renty\n| 26= 26. John I of Craon\n| 27= 27. Marie de Ch\u00e2tillon-sur-Marne\n| 28= 28. [[Frederick of Lorraine, Count of Vaud\u00e9mont]]\n| 29= 29. [[Margaret of Joinville]]\n| 30= 30. [[John VII of Harcourt]]\n| 31= 31. [[Marie of Alen\u00e7on]]\n}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-hou|[[House of Wittelsbach]]|26 November|1462|21 October|1514}}\n{{s-bef|rows=2|before=[[Louis I, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken|Louis I]]}}\n{{s-ttl|rows=1|years=1489&ndash;1514|title=[[Duke and Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken|Duke of Zweibr\u00fccken]]}}\n{{s-aft|rows=1|after=[[Louis II, Count Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken|Louis II]]}}\n{{s-ttl|rows=1|title=[[Count of Veldenz]]|years=1489&ndash;1514}}\n{{s-aft|rows=1|after=[[Rupert, Count Palatine of Veldenz|Rupert]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20071128060836/http://www.gen.heinz-wember.de/wittelsbacher/Alexander1462.htm Die Genealogie der Wittelsbacher ]\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2012}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alexander, Count Palatine Of Zweibrucken}}\n[[Category:1462 births|Wittelsbach, Alexander of Pfalz-Zweibrucken]]\n[[Category:1514 deaths|Wittelsbach, Alexander of Pfalz-Zweibrucken]]\n[[Category:House of Palatinate-Zweibr\u00fccken]]\n[[Category:Christians of the Crusades|Wittelsbach, Alexander of Pfalz-Zweibrucken]]\n[[Category:Counts Palatine of Zweibr\u00fccken]]\n", "name_user": "ArisMethymna", "label": "safe", "comment": "improvements to infobox", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexander,_Count_Palatine_of_Zweibr%C3%BCcken"}
