s dedicated to the [[Two Ewalds]], with statues for the two made in the studio {{ill|Atelier Cuypers-Stoltzenberg|nl}}, owned by Cuypers and Frans Stoltzenberg.<ref>{{cite book|title=Geloof in Nederland: 2000 jaar Nederlanders en hun kerstening|language=nl|page=377|publisher=Waanders/[[Museum Catharijneconvent]]|location=Utrecht|volume=12}}</ref>\n\n== Population centres ==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=10em|\n*[[Afferden, Gelderland|Afferden]]\n*[[Deest]]\n*Druten\n*[[Horssen]]\n*[[Molenhoek, Druten|Molenhoek]]\n*[[Puiflijk]]\n}}\n===Topography===\n[[File:Gem-Druten-OpenTopo.jpg|475px|]]\n\n''Dutch topographic map of the municipality of Druten, June 2015''\n\n==Notable residents==\n* [[Reginald Wolfe]] (died 1573) a Dutch-born English Protestant printer, an original member of the [[Worshipful Company of Stationers and Newspaper Makers|Royal Stationers' Company]]\n* [[Josef van Schaik]] (1882\u20131962) & [[Steef van Schaik]] (1888\u20131968) Dutch politician and brothers\n* [[Peter Hans Kolvenbach]] (1928\u20132016) the twenty-ninth [[Superior General of the Society of Jesus]]\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery mode=packed>\nFile:Druten Kattenburg 39.jpg|Druten Kattenburg 39\nFile:Avondrood in Maas & Waal -sundowner (25747137444).jpg|Avondrood in Maas & Waal\nFile:Druten Beeld Leste Mert.jpg|Druten Beeld Leste Mert\nFile:Druten in Het Land van Maas en Waal met Hatsji-Bratsji's rode toverballon (Franz Karl Ginzkey), ooit de inspiratie van Boudewijn de Groot en Lennaert Nijgh. (Foto- Peter J. Fontijn) (29009370572).jpg|Druten in Het Land van Maas en Waal\nFile:Op de grens- Afferden (4263134185).jpg|Op de grens- Afferden\n</gallery>\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Commons category-inline}}\n*[http://www.druten.nl Official website]\n\n{{Geographic location\n | Centre    = Druten\n | North     = [[Neder-Betuwe]]<br>''[[Waal (river)|Waal]]''\n | East      = [[Beuningen]]\n | Southeast = [[Wijchen]]\n | South     = [[West Maas en Waal]]\n | West      = [[West Maas en Waal]]\n}}\n{{Gelderland Province}}\n\n[[Category:Druten| ]]\n[[Category:Municipalities of Gelderland]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Gelderland]]\n\n{{gelderland-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->\n<!-- Name and transliteration -->\n| name                    = Druten\n| settlement_type         = [[List of municipalities of the Netherlands|Municipality]]\n<!-- Images, nickname, motto -->\n| image_skyline           = Druten, kerk in straatzicht foto12 2010-08-01 12.19.JPG\n| image_alt               = \n| image_caption           = Church in Druten\n| image_flag              = Druten vlag.svg\n| flag_size               = 100x67px\n| flag_alt                = \n| image_shield            = \n| shield_size             = 100x80px\n| shield_alt              = \n<!-- Maps, coordinates -->\n| image_map               = Map - NL - Municipality code 0225 (2009).svg\n| map_alt                 = Highlighted position of Druten in a municipal map of Gelderland\n| map_caption             = Location in Gelderland\n| coordinates             = {{coord|51|53|N|5|36|E|region:NL|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_footnotes   = \n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = [[Netherlands]]\n| subdivision_type1       = [[Provinces of the Netherlands|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1       = [[Gelderland]]\n| government_footnotes    = \n| governing_body          = [[Municipal council (Netherlands)|Municipal council]]\n| leader_party            = PvdA\n| leader_title            = [[Burgemeester|Mayor]]\n| leader_name             = [[Corry van Rhee-Oud Ammerveld]] (acting)\n<!-- Geographic information -->\n| unit_pref               = Metric\n<!-- ALL fields with measurements have automatic unit conversion -->\n<!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| area_footnotes          = <ref>{{Dutch municipality total area|dataref}}</ref>\n<!-- square kilometers -->\n| area_total_km2          = {{Dutch municipality total area|Druten}}\n| area_land_km2           = {{Dutch municipality land area|Druten}}\n| area_water_km2          = {{Dutch municipality water area|Druten}}\n| elevation_footnotes     = <ref name=\"AHN\">{{cite web \n |url = http://www.ahn.nl/postcodetool\n |title = Postcodetool for 6651DA\n |trans-title=|language = Dutch\n |author = <!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> \n |date = \n |work = Actueel Hoogtebestand Nederland\n |publisher = Het Waterschapshuis\n |accessdate = 24 June 2014}}</ref>\n| elevation_m             = 7\n| elevation_max_footnotes = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| elevation_max_m         =\n| elevation_min_footnotes = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags -->\n| elevation_min_m         =\n<!-- Population, demographics -->\n| population_footnotes    = <ref>{{Dutch municipality population|dataref}}</ref>\n| population_total        = {{Dutch municipality population|Druten}}\n| population_as_of        = {{MONTHNAME|{{Dutch municipality population|popbasemonth}}}} {{Dutch municipality population|popbaseyear}}\n| population_density_km2  = {{Dutch municipality population density|Druten}} <!-- For automatic calculation: auto-->\n| population_demonym      = \n<!-- Other information -->\n| timezone                = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset              = +1\n| timezone_DST            = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST          = +2\n| postal_code_type        = [[Postal codes in the Netherlands|Postcode]]\n| postal_code             = 6630\u20136631, 6650\u20136655\n| area_code_type          = [[Telephone numbers in the Netherlands|Area code]]\n| area_code               = 0487\n| website                 = {{URL|1=http://www.druten.nl}}\n| footnotes               =\n}}\n'''Druten''' ({{pronunciation|Nl-Druten.ogg}}) is a [[municipality]] and a town in the eastern [[Netherlands]]. The municipality covers the eastern part of the {{ill|Land van Maas en Waal|nl}} region of the province of [[Gelderland]]. One of its key features is the town's church, designed by architect [[Pierre Cuypers]]. The church is dedicated to the [[Two Ewalds]], with statues for the two made in the studio {{ill|Atelier Cuypers-Stoltzenberg|nl}}, owned by Cuypers and Frans Stoltzenberg.<ref>{{cite book|title=Geloof in Nederland: 2000 jaar Nederlanders en hun kerstening|language=nl|page=377|publisher=Waanders/[[Museum Catharijneconvent]]|location=Utrecht|volume=12}}</ref>\n\n== Population centres ==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=10em|\n*[[Afferden, Gelderland|Afferden]]\n*[[Deest]]\n*Druten\n*[[Horssen]]\n*[[Molenhoek, Druten|Molenhoek]]\n*[[Puiflijk]]\n}}\n===Topography===\n[[File:Gem-Druten-OpenTopo.jpg|475px|]]\n\n''Dutch topographic map of the municipality of Druten, June 2015''\n\n==Notable residents==\n* [[Reginald Wolfe]] (died 1573) a Dutch-born English Protestant printer, an original member of the [[Worshipful Company of Stationers and Newspaper Makers|Royal Stationers' Company]]\n* [[Josef van Schaik]] (1882\u20131962) & [[Steef van Schaik]] (1888\u20131968) Dutch politician and brothers\n* [[Peter Hans Kolvenbach]] (1928\u20132016) the twenty-ninth [[Superior General of the Society of Jesus]]\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery mode=packed>\nFile:Druten Kattenburg 39.jpg|Druten Kattenburg 39\nFile:Avondrood in Maas & Waal -sundowner (25747137444).jpg|Avondrood in Maas & Waal\nFile:Druten Beeld Leste Mert.jpg|Druten Beeld Leste Mert\nFile:Druten in Het Land van Maas en Waal met Hatsji-Bratsji's rode toverballon (Franz Karl Ginzkey), ooit de inspiratie van Boudewijn de Groot en Lennaert Nijgh. (Foto- Peter J. Fontijn) (29009370572).jpg|Druten in Het Land van Maas en Waal\nFile:Op de grens- Afferden (4263134185).jpg|Op de grens- Afferden\n</gallery>\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Commons category-inline}}\n*[http://www.druten.nl Official website]\n\n{{Geographic location\n | Centre    = Druten\n | North     = 