{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran", "text_new": "{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=April 2020}}\n{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Iran}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Iran\n| map1            = COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Iran (Density).svg\n| legend1         = {{legend|#f2a88d|Confirmed cases 10\u201399}}\n{{legend|#e36654|Confirmed cases 100\u2013499}}\n{{legend|#e42a4b|Confirmed cases 500\u2013999}}\n{{legend|#87353f|Confirmed cases 1000\u20139999}}\n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Iran]]\n| first_case      = [[Qom]]\n| arrival_date    = 19 February 2020 <br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month=02|day=19|year=2020}} ago)\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], China (initial reports)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/news/our-columnists/how-iran-became-a-new-epicenter-of-the-coronavirus-outbreak|title=How Iran Became a New Epicenter of the Coronavirus Outbreak|first=Robin|last=Wright|website=The New Yorker|access-date=7 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303213444/https://www.newyorker.com/news/our-columnists/how-iran-became-a-new-epicenter-of-the-coronavirus-outbreak|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| confirmed_cases = 71,686<ref name=\"WorldometerIran\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/country/iran/|title=Iran Coronavirus|website=[[Worldometer]]|access-date=10 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309183228/https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/country/iran/|archive-date=9 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n| deaths          = 4,474<ref name=\"WorldometerIran\"/>\n| recovery_cases  = 43,894<ref name=\"WorldometerIran\"/>\n| suspected_cases = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{URL|http://behdasht.gov.ir/}}\n}}\n\nDuring the [[2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic]], [[:Iran]] reported its first confirmed cases of [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]] infections on 19 February 2020 in [[Qom]].<ref name=\"NYT_Iran_19Feb_first2\" /> As of 10 April 2020, Iran has the sixth-highest number of COVID-19 deaths after Italy, Spain, the United States, France, and the United Kingdom and the eighth-highest number of SARS-CoV-2 cases in the world.{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n\nThe virus may have been brought to the country by a merchant from [[Qom]] who had travelled to China.<ref name=\"newyorker1\"/> Iran became a centre of the spread of the virus in [[the Middle East]],<ref name=\"nyt\"/><ref name=newyorker1 /> with more than ten countries tracing their cases back to Iran by 28 February.<ref name=\"newyorker1\"/> Iran is the worst affected country in the Middle East.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-usa/iran-will-never-ask-us-for-coronavirus-help-official-idUSKBN21O0XI|title=Iran will never ask U.S. for coronavirus help: official|first=Parisa|last=Hafezi|date=6 April 2020|agency=[[Reuters]]}}</ref> The government's actions include cancellation of public events and [[Friday prayers]], closure of schools, universities, shopping centres and bazaars as well as holy shrines, and banning of festival celebrations.<ref name=\"aljeera17012020\">{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/coronavirus-pandemic-kill-millions-iran-200317135500255.html |title=Coronavirus pandemic 'could kill millions' in Iran |date=17 March 2020 |publisher=Al Jazeera |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317222216/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/coronavirus-pandemic-kill-millions-iran-200317135500255.html |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"bbc24032020\" /> Economic measures were also announced to help families and businesses. The government has rejected plans to quarantine entire cities and areas, and heavy traffic between cities continued ahead of [[Nowruz]] despite the government's intention to limit travel. The government later announced a ban on travel between cities following an increase in number of new cases.<ref name=quarantine /><ref name=\"bbc24032020\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-51642926 |title=Coronavirus: Iran is facing a major challenge controlling the outbreak |work=BBC |date=24 March 2020 |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304101128/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-51642926 |archive-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nSome non-Iranian-government sources estimates of the numbers of COVID-19 deaths are much higher than official values.<ref name=\"AJE_Qom_coverup_50deaths\" /><ref name=\"BBC_210_deaths_Iran\" /><ref name=\"france24\"/><ref name=\"JerusalemPost500k\">{{cite web |url=https://www.jpost.com/middle-east/iran-has-500000-coronavirus-infected-people-623832 |title=Iran has 500,000 people infected with coronavirus |first=Benjamin |last=Weinthal |work=Jerusalem Post |date=7 April 2020 |language=en}}</ref> The Iranian government has also been accused of cover-ups, censorship and mismanagement.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/brian-hook-says-iran-lied-to-own-people-over-coronavirus/30470777.html |title=Brian Hook Says Iran 'Lied To Own People' Over Coronavirus |website=Radio Farda |access-date=11 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313124419/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/brian-hook-says-iran-lied-to-own-people-over-coronavirus/30470777.html |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-envoy-says-iran-lied-to-own-people-over-coronavirus/articleshow/74498219.cms|title=US envoy says Iran 'lied to own people' over coronavirus|website=The Times of India|access-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305212012/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/us-envoy-says-iran-lied-to-own-people-over-coronavirus/articleshow/74498219.cms|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jpost.com/Middle-East/Irans-government-and-media-lied-about-coronavirus-outbreak-riots-erupt-618431|title=Iran's government and media lied about coronavirus outbreak|website=The Jerusalem Post|access-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301013021/https://www.jpost.com/Middle-East/Irans-government-and-media-lied-about-coronavirus-outbreak-riots-erupt-618431|archive-date=1 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"newyorker1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.newyorker.com/news/our-columnists/how-iran-became-a-new-epicenter-of-the-coronavirus-outbreak|title=How Iran Became a New Epicenter of the Coronavirus Outbreak|website=The New Yorker|access-date=5 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303213444/https://www.newyorker.com/news/our-columnists/how-iran-became-a-new-epicenter-of-the-coronavirus-outbreak|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> However, the [[World Health Organization]] says that it has not seen problems with Iran's reported figures.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/02/irans-coronavirus-updates-cannot-entirely-be-trusted-expert-says.html|title=Iran's coronavirus updates cannot 'entirely' be trusted, expert says|website=cnbc|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303042553/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/02/irans-coronavirus-updates-cannot-entirely-be-trusted-expert-says.html|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nMultiple Iranian government ministers and senior officials have been diagnosed SARS-CoV-2 positive, as well as 23 members of the [[Islamic Consultative Assembly|Iranian Parliament]] (around 8% of all MPs).<ref name=henley>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/03/iran-steps-up-coronavirus-efforts-as-23-mps-said-to-be-infected |title=Coronavirus: Iran steps up efforts as 23 MPs said to be infected |first=Jon |last=Henley |date=3 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304031109/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/03/iran-steps-up-coronavirus-efforts-as-23-mps-said-to-be-infected |archive-date=4 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> At least 12 sitting or former Iranian politicians and officials had died from the virus by 17 March 2020.<ref name=\"aljeera17012020\"/> Notable individuals reported to have died from COVID-19 include [[Hadi Khosroshahi]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20200227-irans-ex-ambassador-to-vatican-dies-of-coronavirus/ |title=Iran's ex-ambassador to Vatican dies of coronavirus |date=27 February 2020 |work=Middle East Monitor |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305204519/https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20200227-irans-ex-ambassador-to-vatican-dies-of-coronavirus/ |archive-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Mohammad Mirmohammadi]], [[Hossein Sheikholeslam]], [[Fatemeh Rahbar]], [[Reza Mohammadi Langroudi]],<ref name=\"Langroudi\"/> [[Mohammad-Reza Rahchamani]],<ref name=\"Rahchamani\"/> [[Nasser Shabani]],<ref name=\"shabani-dies\"/> [[Hashem Bathaie Golpayegani]],<ref name=\"golpayegani-dies\"/> and [[Hamid Kahram]].<ref name=\"kahram-dies\"/><ref name=\"Ebtekar\" />\n\n== Background ==\nOn 12 January 2020, the [[World Health Organization]] (WHO) confirmed that a [[novel coronavirus]] was the cause of a respiratory illness in a cluster of people in Wuhan City, Hubei Province, China, which was reported to the WHO on 31 December 2019.<ref name=Elsevier>{{cite web |url=https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center |title=Novel Coronavirus Information Center |last=Elsevier |date= |website=Elsevier Connect|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130171622/https://www.elsevier.com/connect/coronavirus-information-center|archive-date=30 January 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Reynolds4March2020>{{Cite news |last=Reynolds |first=Matt |url=https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus |title=What is coronavirus and how close is it to becoming a pandemic? |date=4 March 2020 |work=Wired UK|access-date=5 March 2020 |issn=1357-0978|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305104806/https://www.wired.co.uk/article/china-coronavirus|archive-date=5 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Case fatality rate|case fatality ratio]] for COVID-19 has been much lower than [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome|SARS of 2003]],<ref name=Imperial13March2020>{{cite web |url= https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/ |title=Crunching the numbers for coronavirus |website=Imperial News|access-date=15 March 2020|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200319084913/https://www.imperial.ac.uk/news/196137/crunching-numbers-coronavirus/|archive-date=19 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=Gov.ukHCIDDef>{{cite web |url=https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid |title=High consequence infectious diseases (HCID); Guidance and information about high consequence infectious diseases and their management in England |last= |first= |date= |website=GOV.UK |language=en|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200303051938/https://www.gov.uk/guidance/high-consequence-infectious-diseases-hcid|archive-date=3 March 2020|access-date=17 March 2020}}</ref> but the [[Transmission (medicine)|transmission]] has been significantly greater, with a significant total death toll.<ref name=WFSA>{{cite web |url= https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus |title=World Federation Of Societies of Anaesthesiologists \u2013 Coronavirus |last= |first= |date= |website=www.wfsahq.org|url-status=live|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200312233527/https://www.wfsahq.org/resources/coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=Imperial13March2020/>\n\n==Timeline==\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus outbreak data/Iran medical cases chart}}\n\n===Early cases (19 February - 29 February)===\nOn 19 February, 2 people tested positive for [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|SARS-CoV-2]] in [[Qom]].<ref name=\"NYT_Iran_19Feb_first2\" /> Later that day, the [[Ministry of Health and Medical Education]](MOHME) stated that both had died.<ref name=\"CNBC_Iran_first2deaths\" /> On 20 February,3 new cases were reported by the Ministry of Health. Two of them were from the city of Qom and one from [[Arak, Iran|Arak]].<ref name=\"ThomReut_20Feb_3new\" /> On 21 February, 13 new cases were reported. Seven cases are from Qom, 4 from Tehran, and 2 from [[Gilan Province]]. Two more people in Iran died from COVID-19.<ref name=\"ThomReut_Iran13cases_2moredeaths\" />\nOn 22 February: the Ministry of Health reported 10 more infected cases bringing the total to 29 and two more deaths bringing the total to eight. Eight of the new cases were from the city of Qom and two from Tehran.<ref name=\"ThomReut_10new_2deaths\" /> The following day Iran's Health Minister [[Saeed Namaki]] said that one of those who died was a merchant from Qom who traveled regularly using indirect flights between China and Iran after direct flights were suspended between the two countries, and may have brought the virus from China.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-s-health-minister-says-virus-came-from-china-travel/30449759.html |title=Iran's Health Minister Says Virus Came From China Travel |date=23 February 2020 |work=Radio Farda |access-date=29 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224162650/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-s-health-minister-says-virus-came-from-china-travel/30449759.html |archive-date=24 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAccording to the report on 25 February, the Iranian government first told Iranian citizens that the U.S. had \"hyped COVID-19 to suppress turnout\" during its government elections, and that it would \"punish anyone spreading rumors about a serious epidemic.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/irans-coronavirus-problem-lot-worse-it-seems/607663/|title=Iran Has Far More Coronavirus Cases Than It Is Letting On|website=The Atlantic|access-date=9 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309232036/https://www.theatlantic.com/ideas/archive/2020/03/irans-coronavirus-problem-lot-worse-it-seems/607663/|archive-date=9 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/coronavirus-iran-struggles-contain-outbreak-how-why-photos-2020-3?IR=T#supreme-leader-ali-khamenei-has-also-been-pictured-wearing-disposable-gloves-during-a-speech-an-apparent-health-measure-that-he-hadnt-appeared-to-take-before-7|title=From silencing medics to banning 'rumors': Here's why Iran is struggling to contain its coronavirus outbreak|website=Business Insider|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315080511/https://www.businessinsider.com/coronavirus-iran-struggles-contain-outbreak-how-why-photos-2020-3?IR=T#supreme-leader-ali-khamenei-has-also-been-pictured-wearing-disposable-gloves-during-a-speech-an-apparent-health-measure-that-he-hadnt-appeared-to-take-before-7|archive-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nationalreview.com/news/iran-to-sentence-citizens-who-spreads-rumors-about-coronavirus-to-flogging-three-years-in-prison/|title=Iran to Sentence Citizens Who 'Spreads Rumors' about Coronavirus to Flogging, Three Years in Prison|website=National Review|date=26 February 2020|access-date=13 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310160903/https://www.nationalreview.com/news/iran-to-sentence-citizens-who-spreads-rumors-about-coronavirus-to-flogging-three-years-in-prison/|archive-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> A closed parliamentary session including Health Minister [[Saeed Namaki]] and Ahmad Amirabadi Farahani was held. Body temperatures were tested prior to the meeting and three members of parliament, including Amirabadi Farahani, were requested to excuse themselves from the session and self-quarantine. All three attended the session. Amirabadi Farahani later spoke with journalists and gave television interviews wearing a mask and pair of gloves.<ref name=\"AlArabiya_Amirabadi_symptoms\">{{cite news|url= https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/24/Iranian-MP-50-dead-from-coronavirus-in-Qom-Health-Minister-to-blame-ILNA.html |title=About 50 dead from coronavirus in Qom, Health Minister to blame: Iran MP on ILNA |date= 25 February 2020 |publisher=[[Al Arabiya]] |accessdate=25 February 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200225132649/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/24/Iranian-MP-50-dead-from-coronavirus-in-Qom-Health-Minister-to-blame-ILNA.html |archivedate= 25 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> As the Ministry of Health reported, there were totally 593 infected and confirmed cases and 43 death up to 29 February.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.farsnews.ir/newstext.aspx?nn=13981207000699 |title=Health Ministry Raises Number of Coronavirus-Infected People in Iran to 139, Fatalities to 19 | date=26 February 2020|agency=FARS News Agency}}</ref><ref name=\"MOH27FebA\">{{cite web |title=\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0633\u0627\u06cc\u06cc 106 \u0628\u06cc\u0645\u0627\u0631 \u062c\u062f\u06cc\u062f \u06a9\u0648\u0648\u06cc\u062f19 \u062f\u0631 \u06a9\u0634\u0648\u0631 |url=http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=54782&newsview=199991 |website=behdasht.gov |accessdate=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227163707/http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=54782&newsview=199991 |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n<ref name=\"MOH28Feb\"/><ref>{{cite web|url= http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200039 |title=\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a\u060c \u062f\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634 \u067e\u0632\u0634\u0643\u064a |website=behdasht.gov.ir |accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n[[Image:3408162 \u0628\u062e\u0634 \u0648\u06cc\u0698\u0647 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0628\u06cc\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0647\u0627\u062c\u0631.jpg|thumb|250px|A patient receiving treatment in a hospital in [[Tehran]]]]\n\n===Three weeks before Nowruz (1 March - 19 March)===\n[[File:CoViD-19 IR.svg|thumb|Right|upright=2|Number of cases (blue) and number of deaths (red) on a [[logarithmic scale]].]]\nOn 1 March, the Ministry of Health reported 385 more new confirmed cases and 11 new deaths. He also reported that 52 more people have recovered, bringing the total number to 175.<ref name=\"Behdasht_523cases_12deaths_2Mar\" />On 11 March, According to the Ministry of Health's report, there were 9000 new confirmed cases and 354 deaths.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200188|title=\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a\u060c \u062f\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634 \u067e\u0632\u0634\u0643\u064a|website=behdasht.gov.ir|accessdate=8 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303001521/http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200188|archive-date=3 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200252|title=\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a\u060c \u062f\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634 \u067e\u0632\u0634\u0643\u064a|website=behdasht.gov.ir|accessdate=8 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310050601/http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200252|archive-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200306|title=\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a\u060c \u062f\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634 \u067e\u0632\u0634\u0643\u064a|website=behdasht.gov.ir|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://behdasht.gov.ir/index.jsp?siteid=1&fkeyid=&siteid=1&pageid=55373&newsview=200330|title=\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a\u060c \u062f\u0631\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0648 \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634 \u067e\u0632\u0634\u0643\u064a|website=behdasht.gov.ir|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://ifpnews.com/coronavirus-kills-record-breaking-number-of-iranians-in-24-hours |title=Coronavirus Kills Record-Breaking Number of Iranians in 24 Hours |website=IFP News |date=10 March 2020 |access-date=11 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311155042/https://ifpnews.com/coronavirus-kills-record-breaking-number-of-iranians-in-24-hours |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> They also reported that a total of 2,959 patients had recovered so far. Hassan Rouhani, Iran's President, has assumed the chairmanship of the national taskforce on combatting the outbreak of the novel Coronavirus, replacing the Health Minister at the request of lawmakers.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ifpnews.com/rouhani-to-chair-irans-taskforce-on-combatting-coronavirus|title=Rouhani to Chair Iran's Taskforce on Combatting Coronavirus|website=IFP News|date=11 March 2020|access-date=11 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312175854/https://ifpnews.com/rouhani-to-chair-irans-taskforce-on-combatting-coronavirus|archive-date=12 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[Image:13981225000552637198764368440415 \u0647\u0634\u062f\u0627\u0631\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u00ab\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627\u06cc\u06cc\u00bb \u062f\u0631 \u0634\u0647\u0631.jpg|thumb|250px|People in [[Shiraz]] wearing facemasks next to a closed market]]\n\nOn 12 March, the Ministry of Health reported 1,075 more new confirmed cases and 75 new deaths. They also reported that 3,276 people had recovered so far.Iran requested an emergency loan of US$5&nbsp;billion from the [[International Monetary Fund]] for the first time since the 1960s to help combat the virus outbreak.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/03/12/iran-request-5-billion-emergency-loan-international-monetary/ |title=Iran requests $5&nbsp;billion emergency loan from International Monetary Fund to fight coronavirus pandemic |first=Roland |last=Oliphant |date=12 March 2020 |work=The Telegraph |access-date=13 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314013011/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/03/12/iran-request-5-billion-emergency-loan-international-monetary/ |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> \"The American government of opposing efforts by the International Monetary Fund to assist Iran during the pandemic\",Ali Shamkhani, secretary of Iran's Supreme National Security Council, said.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/04/dangerous-coronavirus-iranian-admiral-200406064200587.html |title='Trump more dangerous than coronavirus': Iranian admiral |work= aljazeera|date=6 April 2020  }}</ref> On 17 March, the Ministry of Health reported 1,178 more new confirmed cases and 135 new deaths. They also reported that 5,389 people had recovered so far. [[Sharif University]] published a study over number of possible casualties. Three scenarios were announced: If people cooperate now, Iran will see 120,000 infections and 12,000 deaths before the outbreak is over, if they offer medium cooperation, there will be 300,000 cases and 110,000 deaths. But if people fail to follow any guidance, it could collapse Iran's already strained medical system and there will be 4 million cases and 3.5 million deaths.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apnews.com/6e92d93551ee6c6ae51d0acaaad9eb32|title=Iran warns virus could kill 'millions' in Islamic Republic|date=17 March 2020|website=AP NEWS|access-date=17 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318132446/https://apnews.com/6e92d93551ee6c6ae51d0acaaad9eb32|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Until 19 March, 18407 more confirmed cases and 1284 deaths were reported by the Ministry of Health.{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n\n===Nowruz, a new peak (20 March - 3 April)===\nOn 20 March, 1,237 new infections and 149 deaths were reported.{{cn|date=April 2020}} On 24 March, a new peak of 1,762 new cases were announced with 122 deaths reported.  President Rouhani said that the number of patients admitted to hospitals in different provinces as well as deaths due to the virus had decreased, which he took to be promising.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/446297/Rouhani-claims-number-of-coronavirus-patients-deaths-decreasing |title=Rouhani claims number of coronavirus patients, deaths decreasing |date=24 March 2020 |work=Tehran Times |access-date=28 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328140136/https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/446297/Rouhani-claims-number-of-coronavirus-patients-deaths-decreasing |archive-date=28 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Iran accused [[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res]] of being spies, and a team they had sent to Iran to help had been ordered to leave the country.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.msf.org/msf-surprised-iran-put-stop-our-covid-19-response |title=MSF 'deeply surprised' that Iranian authorities put a stop to our COVID-19 response |date=25 March 2020 |work=Medecins Sans Frontieres |access-date=27 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327131927/https://www.msf.org/msf-surprised-iran-put-stop-our-covid-19-response |archive-date=27 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-rejects-foreign-virus-death-toll-nears-2000-200324202829056.html |title=Iran rejects 'foreign' help as virus death toll nears 2,000 |date=24 March 2020 |publisher=Al Jazeera |access-date=28 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200330011513/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-rejects-foreign-virus-death-toll-nears-2000-200324202829056.html |archive-date=30 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 25 March, with new cases surpassing 2,000 for the first time, the government warned of a \"second wave\" of infection.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-52039298 |title=Coronavirus: Iran bans internal travel to avert 'second wave' |date=25 March 2020 |work=BBC |access-date=27 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327191650/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-52039298 |archive-date=27 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 26 March, Iranian Health Ministry announced that 2,389 more people had become infected, with 157 new deaths.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-toll/irans-death-toll-from-coronavirus-climbs-to-2234-ministry-idUSKBN21D18F |title= Iran's death toll from coronavirus climbs to 2,234: ministry |agency= Reuters |date= 26 March 2020 |access-date= 27 March 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200327130147/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-toll/irans-death-toll-from-coronavirus-climbs-to-2234-ministry-idUSKBN21D18F |archive-date= 27 March 2020 |url-status= live }}</ref>On 27 March, daily new cases had increased to 2,926 with 144 deaths.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/03/27/world/middleeast/27reuters-health-coronavirus-iran.html|title=Iran's Death Toll From Coronavirus Rises to 2,378: Health Ministry|date=27 March 2020|agency=Reuters|work=The New York Times|access-date=27 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327132735/https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/03/27/world/middleeast/27reuters-health-coronavirus-iran.html|archive-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Iranian media reported that nearly 300 people had died and over a thousand became ill due to [[methanol poisoning]] in the belief that drinking the alcohol can kill the virus in the body. [[Associated Press]] gave figures of around 480 deaths and 2,850 others affected.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2020/03/27/world/middleeast/ap-ml-virus-outbreak-iran-a-deadly-drink.html|title=In Iran, False Belief a Poison Fights Virus Kills Hundreds|agency=Associated Press|work=The New York Times|date=27 March 2020|access-date=27 March 2020|archive-date=27 March 2020|archive-url=https://archive.today/20200327190836/https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2020/03/27/world/middleeast/ap-ml-virus-outbreak-iran-a-deadly-drink.html|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 March, the number of new cases exceeded 3,000 for the first time (3,076), with 139 reported new deaths.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/iran-coronavirus-death-toll-rises-to-2-517/1783000 |title=Iran: Coronavirus death toll rises to 2,517first=Ahmet |last=Dursun |date=28 March 2020 |publisher=Analou Agency |access-date=28 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328101714/https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/iran-coronavirus-death-toll-rises-to-2-517/1783000 |archive-date=28 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 29 March, 2,901 new cases and 123 new deaths were announced.<ref name=\"irna-29march\">{{cite news|url=https://en.irna.ir/news/83731895/Official-12-391-COVID19-infected-patients-recovered-in-Iran|title=Official: 12,391 COVID19-infected patients recovered in Iran|agency=Islamic Republic News Agency|date=29 March 2020|access-date=29 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329110432/https://en.irna.ir/news/83731895/Official-12-391-COVID19-infected-patients-recovered-in-Iran|archive-date=29 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> President Rouhani defended his government's response to the crisis, and said that according to health experts and doctors in Iran, \"in some provinces, we have passed the peak [of the epidemic] and are on a downward trajectory\".<ref name=\"aljazeera29032020\">{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-coronavirus-deaths-rise-rouhani-hits-criticism-200329113250455.html |title=As Iran coronavirus deaths rise, Rouhani hits back at criticism |date=29 March 2020 |publisher=Al Jazeera |access-date=29 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200329150548/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-coronavirus-deaths-rise-rouhani-hits-criticism-200329113250455.html |archive-date=29 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 2 April \u2013 President Rouhani warned that the country could fight the coronavirus pandemic for another year. 3,111 new infections raise Iran's total to 50,468. 124 new deaths bring the total to 3,160. 16,711 of those hospitalised have recovered.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/iran-warns-months-crisis-virus-deaths-reach-3-111855260.html Iran warns of months of crisis as virus deaths reach 3,160] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403213056/https://news.yahoo.com/iran-warns-months-crisis-virus-deaths-reach-3-111855260.html |date=3 April 2020 }} AFP, 2 April 2020</ref>\n\n===After Nowruz (4 April - Up to now)===\nOn 7 April, Jahanpour stated that the intensification of the social distancing policy leads to decreasing the number of new cases in recent days. In order to don't \u201cput back in a difficult situation\u201d, President Hassan Rouhani asked people again \"to stay at home\" and obey guidelines.<ref name=\"timesofisrael2020\"/>\n\nAs IRNA reported, the  \u201clow-risk\u201d business activities reopened in most of the country on 11 April, \"exception of the capital Tehran, where they will re-open from April 18\".Rouhani said  \u201cEasing restrictions does not mean ignoring health protocols ... Social distancing and other health protocols should be respected seriously by people.\u201d In order to follow the social distancing, \"Many government offices also re-opened, with two-thirds of their staff\" on 11 April. Theatres, swimming pools, saunas, beauty salons, schools, shopping centers, and restaurants, as high-risk businesses, have not to resume. \"Schools and universities remain closed\", and cultural, religious and sports gatherings have been banned. In another hand, According to health authorities,\"many Iranians have ignored appeals to stay at home, warning of a second wave of the outbreak.\"<ref>{{cite web |title=Iran renews coronavirus warning as 'low risk' activities re-start |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/iran-renews-coronavirus-warning-as-low-risk-activities-re-start-idUSKCN21T0AO |website=reuters |accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Government response ==\n[[Image:13981205000415637181505100958241 \u0646\u0634\u0633\u062a \u062e\u0628\u0631\u06cc \u0633\u062e\u0646\u06af\u0648\u06cc \u062f\u0648\u0644\u062a.jpg|thumb|250px|Spokesperson of the Government [[Ali Rabiei]] and Deputy Health Minister [[Iraj Harirchi]] at a press conference. Hours after the conference, it was announced that Harirchi himself tested positive for the virus.]]\nOn 23 March 2020, Iran's [[Supreme Leader of Iran|Supreme Leader]] Ayatollah [[Ali Khamenei]] mentioned a [[conspiracy theory]] that the US created \"a special version\" of the virus that was affecting the country, adding \"I do not know how real this accusation is\".<ref name=aj/><ref name=\"1 April 2020\">{{cite web |title=Iran Says U.S. Sanctions Are Taking Lives. U.S. Officials Disagree. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/01/world/middleeast/iran-virus-sanctions.html |website=NYT |access-date=6 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402173016/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/01/world/middleeast/iran-virus-sanctions.html |archive-date=2 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: Iran's leader suggests US cooked up 'special version' of virus to target country |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/iran-coronavirus-us-target-country-special-version-covid19-a9417206.html |work=The Independent |date=23 March 2020 |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324095310/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/iran-coronavirus-us-target-country-special-version-covid19-a9417206.html |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Khamenei said that the virus outbreak may be a \"biological attack\" on Iran.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-12/iran-s-khamenei-says-virus-outbreak-may-be-biological-attack |title=Iran's Khamenei Says Virus Outbreak May Be 'Biological Attack' |first1=Yasna |last1=Haghdoost |first2=Golnar |last2=Motevalli |work=Bloomberg |access-date=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323123634/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-12/iran-s-khamenei-says-virus-outbreak-may-be-biological-attack |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Major General [[Hossein Salami|Salami]], Commander of the [[Islamic Revolution Guards Corps]], stated \"Iran is currently engaged in [[biological warfare]] and will definitely win the war\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/en/news/2020/03/05/2217376/iran-involved-in-biological-warfare-irgc-chief/amp|title=Iran Involved in Biological Warfare: IRGC Chief \u2013 Politics news|agency=Tasnim News Agency|access-date=6 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307051241/https://www.tasnimnews.com/en/news/2020/03/05/2217376/iran-involved-in-biological-warfare-irgc-chief/amp|archive-date=7 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> These claims were seen by many, including the [[Anti-Defamation League]] (ADL), as being [[Antisemitism|anti-semititic]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=FRANTZMAN|first1=SETH|url=https://www.jpost.com/Middle-East/Iran-News/Irans-regime-pushes-antisemitic-conspiracies-about-coronavirus-620212|title=Iran's regime pushes antisemitic conspiracies about coronavirus|date=8 March 2020|work=J Post|accessdate=24 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310213820/https://www.jpost.com/Middle-East/Iran-News/Irans-regime-pushes-antisemitic-conspiracies-about-coronavirus-620212|archive-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=|first1=|url=https://www.ifcj.org/news/stand-for-israel/iran-pushes-anti-semitic-theories-on-coronavirus/|title=Iran Pushes Anti-Semitic Theories on Coronavirus|date=8 March 2020|work=[[International Fellowship of Christians and Jews]]|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nPresident Rouhani, however, said on 26 February 2020 that there are no plans to quarantine areas affected by the outbreak, and only individuals would be quarantined.<ref name=quarantine>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-51651454 |title=Coronavirus: Iran has no plans to quarantine cities, Rouhani says |work=BBC |date=26 February 2020 |access-date=26 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226194202/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-51651454 |archive-date=26 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>On 1 April, Hassan Rouhani told that \"Iranians had done \"great work\" and that the outbreak appeared to be receding in all provinces\".He said that Iran is one of the much more successful country in comparison with others to control the virus while The US have imposed sanctions.<ref name= bbcmarch/>\n\nOn 26 February, [[Iranian Cyber Police]] announced that to stop spreading photos and videos which are untrue and fake on coronavirus, notices were given to 118 people and 24 others were arrested.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0628\u06cc\u0633\u062a \u0648 \u0686\u0647\u0627\u0631 \u0634\u0627\u06cc\u0639\u0647 \u067e\u0631\u0627\u06a9\u0646 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u062f\u0633\u062a\u06af\u06cc\u0631 \u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f |url=https://www.tabnak.ir/fa/news/961993/\u06f2\u06f4-\u0634\u0627\u06cc\u0639\u0647-\u067e\u0631\u0627\u06a9\u0646-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627-\u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633-\u062f\u0633\u062a\u06af\u06cc\u0631-\u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f |website=tabnak.ir |accessdate=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303042943/https://www.tabnak.ir/fa/news/961993/%DB%B2%DB%B4-%D8%B4%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B9%D9%87-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%A7%DA%A9%D9%86-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7-%D9%88%DB%8C%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3-%D8%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%DA%AF%DB%8C%D8%B1-%D8%B4%D8%AF%D9%86%D8%AF |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> These indictments were considered vague by [[Article 19]],<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646: \u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0632 \u0628\u0647 \u06af\u0631\u062f\u0634 \u0622\u0632\u0627\u062f \u0627\u0637\u0644\u0627\u0639\u0627\u062a \u0631\u0627 \u0645\u0647\u0645 \u062a\u0631 \u0645\u06cc\u200c\u06a9\u0646\u062f |url=https://www.article19.org/fa/resources/iran-coronavirus-crisis-highlights-need-for-the-free-flow-of-information/ |website=ARTICLE 19 |accessdate=6 March 2020 |language=fa-IR |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306205645/https://www.article19.org/fa/resources/iran-coronavirus-crisis-highlights-need-for-the-free-flow-of-information/ |archive-date=6 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> and the government's attempt to control the information flow.{{citation needed|date=March 2020}} Iranian football player [[Mohammad Mokhtari (footballer)|Mohammad Mokhtari]] who on 10 March had posted on Instagram, criticising the authorities\u2019 handling of the coronavirus outbreak was arrested by the [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Iran arrests footballer over coronavirus Instagram posts |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/13/Iran-arrests-footballer-over-coronavirus-Instagram-posts-.html |accessdate=13 March 2020 |agency=[[Al Arabiya English]] |date=13 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314152214/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/13/Iran-arrests-footballer-over-coronavirus-Instagram-posts-.html |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 14 March, he was released after offering expressions of regret.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tabnak.ir/fa/news/965850/%DA%A9%D8%A7%D9%BE%DB%8C%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B4-%DA%AF%DB%8C%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A2%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%AF-%D8%B4%D8%AF |title=\u06a9\u0627\u067e\u06cc\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u062f\u0627\u0645\u0627\u0634 \u06af\u06cc\u0644\u0627\u0646 \u0622\u0632\u0627\u062f \u0634\u062f |work=Tabnak |date=14 March 2020 |access-date=25 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315165920/https://www.tabnak.ir/fa/news/965850/%DA%A9%D8%A7%D9%BE%DB%8C%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B4-%DA%AF%DB%8C%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A2%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%AF-%D8%B4%D8%AF |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Healthcare action===\n[[Image:\u0639\u0645\u0644\u06cc\u0627\u062a \u0636\u062f\u0639\u0641\u0648\u0646\u06cc \u0645\u0639\u0627\u0628\u0631 \u0639\u0645\u0648\u0645\u06cc \u0648 \u0634\u0647\u0631\u06cc \u0645\u062d\u0644\u0647 \u0646\u0628\u0631\u062f \u062a\u0647\u0631\u0627\u0646.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Disinfection of [[Piroozi]], Tehran]]\nOn 2 March 2020, the government announced plans to mobilise 300,000 soldiers and volunteers to combat the spread of the virus, as well as deploying drones and water cannon to disinfect streets.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-mobilizes-300-000-people-and-deploys-drones-and-water-cannon-to-halt-the-spread-of-coronavirus-11583157765 |title=Iran Mobilizes 300,000 Teams and Deploys Drones and Water Cannon to Halt the Spread of Coronavirus |first1=Aresu |last1=Eqbali |first2=Isabel |last2=Coles |date=2 March 2020 |work=The Wall Street Journal |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303152213/https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-mobilizes-300-000-people-and-deploys-drones-and-water-cannon-to-halt-the-spread-of-coronavirus-11583157765 |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>On 13 March 2020, plan to clear streets, shops and public places in Iran by the Revolutionary Guards was announced. In addition, 1,000 fixed and mobile detection clinics would be set up, the army would work alongside medical staff as well as producing face masks and gloves, and army beds would be made available for patients.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/13/revolutionary-guards-enforce-coronavirus-controls-iran |title=Revolutionary Guards to enforce coronavirus controls in Iran |first=Patrick |last=Wintour=13 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=14 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314135322/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/13/revolutionary-guards-enforce-coronavirus-controls-iran |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe head of the Medical Council of the Islamic Republic of Iran, Dr. Mohammad Reza Zafarghandi, said on 18 March that 22&nbsp;million Iranians had been screened and that the condition of a million and a half is being monitored. He also said the numbers given by the Health Ministry are those of confirmed cases, adding, \"The reality is the real numbers are higher than the [reported] numbers.\"\n<ref>{{cite web|title=Iran medical council says coronavirus crisis still developing |url=https://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2020/03/iran-medical-council-coronavirus-peak.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320173253/https://www.al-monitor.com/pulse/originals/2020/03/iran-medical-council-coronavirus-peak.html |archivedate=20 March 2020|date=20 March 2020 }}</ref>The [[Ministry of Defence and Armed Forces Logistics (Iran)|Ministry of Defense and Armed Forces Logistics]] created the first COVID-19 test kit on 23 February.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ir.sputniknews.com/iran/202002235998625-\u062a\u0648\u0644\u06cc\u062f-\u0646\u062e\u0633\u062a\u06cc\u0646-\u06a9\u06cc\u062a-\u062a\u0634\u062e\u06cc\u0635-\u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627-\u062f\u0631-\u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646/|title=\u062a\u0648\u0644\u06cc\u062f \u0646\u062e\u0633\u062a\u06cc\u0646 \u06a9\u06cc\u062a \u062a\u0634\u062e\u06cc\u0635 \u0648\u06cc\u0631\u0648\u0633 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631 \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646|agency=Sputnik News Agency|language=fa|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224175254/https://ir.sputniknews.com/iran/202002235998625-%D8%AA%D9%88%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%AF-%D9%86%D8%AE%D8%B3%D8%AA%DB%8C%D9%86-%DA%A9%DB%8C%D8%AA-%D8%AA%D8%B4%D8%AE%DB%8C%D8%B5-%D9%88%DB%8C%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B3-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%AF%D8%B1-%D8%A7%DB%8C%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86/|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The government created an application and a website to combat the outbreak.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://digiato.com/article/2020/03/04/\u0627\u067e\u0644\u06cc\u06a9\u06cc\u0634\u0646-\u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647-\u0628\u0627-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627-\u0639\u0631\u0636\u0647-\u0634\u062f\u061b-\u0627\u0632-\u0627\u0646/|title=\u0633\u0627\u0645\u0627\u0646\u0647 \u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0627 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u0639\u0631\u0636\u0647 \u0634\u062f\u061b \u0627\u0632 \u0627\u0646\u062c\u0627\u0645 \u062a\u0633\u062a\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0627\u0648\u0644\u06cc\u0647 \u062a\u0627 \u0648\u06cc\u062f\u06cc\u0648\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634\u06cc|website=\u062f\u06cc\u062c\u06cc\u0627\u062a\u0648|accessdate=8 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315113431/https://digiato.com/article/2020/03/04/%D8%A7%D9%BE%D9%84%DB%8C%DA%A9%DB%8C%D8%B4%D9%86-%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%84%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%B6%D9%87-%D8%B4%D8%AF%D8%9B-%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%A7%D9%86/|archive-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nCitizens were also advised to avoid using banknotes.<ref NAME=BBC52020>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-51760563|title=Coronavirus: Iran limits travel and urges banknote avoidance|date=5 March 2020|work=BBC|access-date=6 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306115643/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-51760563|archive-date=6 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====Prisons====\nThe Iranian judiciary spokesman, Gholam Hossein Ismaili said that \"he was activating a range of preventive measures including cutting the number of people being sent to jail and allowing some inmates out on temporary early release.\"<ref name=\"Guard_NZagRatc_possible_COVID19\">{{cite news |first1=Mattha |last1=Busby |first2=Michael |last2=Safi |title=Nazanin Zaghari-Ratcliffe suspected of having coronavirus |url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2020/feb/29/nazanin-zaghari-ratcliffe-family-believe-she-has-coronavirus |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=29 February 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200301233032/https://www.theguardian.com/news/2020/feb/29/nazanin-zaghari-ratcliffe-family-believe-she-has-coronavirus |archivedate=1 March 2020 |url-status=live |date=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March 2020, around 70,000 prisoners were temporarily released from prisons due to the outbreak ostensibly to limit the further spread of the disease within prisons.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/italy-coronavirus-toll-soars-north-sealed-live-updates-200308235426110.html |title=Iran releases 70,000 prisoners as toll rises: Live updates |first1=Kate |