ronavirus |archivedate=1 March 2020 |url-status=live |date=29 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 March 2020, around 70,000 prisoners were temporarily released from prisons due to the outbreak ostensibly to limit the further spread of the disease within prisons.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/italy-coronavirus-toll-soars-north-sealed-live-updates-200308235426110.html |title=Iran releases 70,000 prisoners as toll rises: Live updates |first1=Kate |last1=Mayberry |first2=Virginia |last2=Pietromarchi |publisher=Al Jazeera |date=9 March 2020 |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309135638/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/italy-coronavirus-toll-soars-north-sealed-live-updates-200308235426110.html |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/iran-temporarily-releases-70000-prisoners-as-coronavirus-cases-surge-idUSKBN20W1E5 |title=Iran temporarily releases 70,000 prisoners as coronavirus cases surge |agency=[[Reuters]] |date=9 March 2020 |access-date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310071208/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/iran-temporarily-releases-70000-prisoners-as-coronavirus-cases-surge-idUSKBN20W1E5 |archive-date=10 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 10 March,More than 54,000 prisoners were temporarily released to prevent the spread of coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51723398 |title=Coronavirus: Iran temporarily frees 54,000 prisoners to combat spread |work=BBC News |date=3 March 2020 |access-date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200305001254/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51723398 |archive-date=5 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>On 17 March, About 85,000 prisoners were temporarily released due to the coronavirus,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-iran-frees-85-000-prisoners-to-combat-spread-of-covid-19-11958783 |title=Iran temporarily frees 85,000 from jail, including political prisoners, amid coronavirus |first=Parisa |last=Hafezi |date=17 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317144133/https://news.sky.com/story/coronavirus-iran-frees-85-000-prisoners-to-combat-spread-of-covid-19-11958783 |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> and two days later the government announced plans to pardon 11,000 prisoners, including those charged with political crimes.<ref>{{cite news |title=Iran frees 85,000 prisoners due to coronavirus, says judiciary spokesman |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/17/Iran-frees-85-000-prisoners-due-to-coronavirus-says-judiciary-spokesman.html |accessdate=18 March 2020 |agency=Al Arabiya English |date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318141153/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/17/Iran-frees-85-000-prisoners-due-to-coronavirus-says-judiciary-spokesman.html |archive-date=18 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/19/iran-to-pardon-10000-including-security-prisoners |title=Iran to pardon 10,000, including 'security' prisoners |first=Patrick |last=Wintour |date=19 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320191918/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/19/iran-to-pardon-10000-including-security-prisoners |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 27 March,  70 inmates escaped Saqqez Prison in Kurdistan province.<ref name=riot_iran />On 28 March Prisoners in the [[western Iran]]ian city of [[Hamadan]] rioted and escaped, using the coronavirus outbreak as a pretext according to Hamedan's prosecutor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irna.ir/news/83732426/\u062f\u0627\u062f\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646-\u0647\u0645\u062f\u0627\u0646-\u0644\u06cc\u062f\u0631\u0647\u0627\u06cc-\u0646\u0627\u0622\u0631\u0627\u0645\u06cc-\u062f\u0631-\u0632\u0646\u062f\u0627\u0646-\u0627\u06cc\u0646-\u0634\u0647\u0631-\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0633\u0627\u06cc\u06cc-\u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f|title=\u062f\u0627\u062f\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646 \u0647\u0645\u062f\u0627\u0646: \u0644\u06cc\u062f\u0631\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0646\u0627\u0622\u0631\u0627\u0645\u06cc \u062f\u0631 \u0632\u0646\u062f\u0627\u0646 \u0627\u06cc\u0646 \u0634\u0647\u0631 \u0634\u0646\u0627\u0633\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u0634\u062f\u0646\u062f |work=IRNA}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/coronavirus-iran-says-54-inmates-large-after-mass-jail-break |title=Coronavirus: Iran says 54 inmates at large after mass jail break |date=30 March 2020 |work=Middle East Eye |access-date=5 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401002213/https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/coronavirus-iran-says-54-inmates-large-after-mass-jail-break |archive-date=1 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Prisoners in the city of [[Mahabad]], in Iran's [[Kurds|Kurdish]] region, also attempted to escape.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.avatoday.net/node/9307|title=More attempts of prison break reported from Iran &#124; AvaToday|website=www.avatoday.net|accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref> On 30 March, there was a [[Impact of the 2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic on prisons|prison riot]] in the south of the country.100,000 prisoners have been released as a measure to contain the pandemic, but an estimated 50,000 people are still behind bars, including violent offenders and so called \"security cases\",dual nationals and others with Western ties.<ref name=riot_iran>[https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/jordan-releases-travelers-quarantined-dead-sea-hotels-69867295?cid=clicksource_76_null_headlines_hed Prisoners riot in Iran; Netanyahu goes into self-quarantine] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402170513/https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/jordan-releases-travelers-quarantined-dead-sea-hotels-69867295?cid=clicksource_76_null_headlines_hed |date=2 April 2020 }} By AMIR VAHDAT and ARON HELLER, Associated Press, 30 March 2020</ref> Human rights activists have reported that during riots in different Iran's jails on 30 and 31 March, at least 20 prisoners were killed in two prisons in [[Ahwaz]], when the guards opened fire of the prisoners. Several other prisoners are reported killed in Shiban prison, also in Ahwaz.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/activists-say-many-inmates-killed-in-iran-prison-disturbances/30523805.html |title=Activists Say Many Inmates Killed In Iran Prison Disturbances |access-date=3 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404055214/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/activists-say-many-inmates-killed-in-iran-prison-disturbances/30523805.html |archive-date=4 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 3 April 2020, Rupert Colville, a spokesman for the [[United Nations Human Rights Commission]] expressed his worries about prison conditions in \"countries including Iran, one of the worst-hit in the world\". There have been riots in the prisons of Iran and some other countries, \"prisoners who are afraid, who are distressed at the big loss of contact from family members and so on. So, there are many, many issues surrounding this\". Colville's comment came after Daniel Zeinolabedini, juvenile offender, an inmate in [[Mahabad]] prison, north east of Iran, died after he was reportedly badly beaten by prison guards.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/un-high-commissioner-horrified-at-death-of-young-man-in-iran-prison/30529032.html |title=UN High Commissioner 'Horrified' At Death Of Young Man In Iran Prison |access-date=4 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404055227/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/un-high-commissioner-horrified-at-death-of-young-man-in-iran-prison/30529032.html |archive-date=4 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=U.N. Worried About Iran Prisoners Amid Coronavirus Outbreak |url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/04/03/world/middleeast/03reuters-health-coronavirus-iran.html |website=NYT |accessdate=3 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403164016/https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/04/03/world/middleeast/03reuters-health-coronavirus-iran.html |archive-date=3 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>There has been riot erupted on 28 March, before Daniel's death, Prisoners were protesting at prison conditions and the failure of the authorities to temporarily release them amid the COVID-19 pandemic.<ref>[https://www.ohchr.org/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID=25773&LangID=E Press briefing note on Iran]</ref>\n\n7 April 2020 Iranian authorities have displaced some of [[political prisoners]] from Shiban prisons in Ahwaz to an unknown location. This is after the [[protest]]s that occurred on 30 and 31 March inside Iran's prisons due to lack of medical facilities to encounter the spread of [[Coronavirus]]. According to the Radio Farda, the regime severely suppressed the protests and a number of prisoners were killed. <ref>[https://en.radiofarda.com/a/dozens-of-political-prisoners-in-iran-moved-to-unknown-location-after-unrest-/30540347.html Dozens Of Political Prisoners In Iran Moved To Unknown Location After Unrest]</ref>\n\n===Cancellations===\n\n====Cultural and Sporting event, closing of public places ====\nThe [[Ministry of Sport and Youth (Iran)|Ministry of Sports and Youth]] took steps to cancel sporting events, including football matches.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.varzesh3.com/news/1669982/\u0644\u063a\u0648-\u0647\u0645\u0647-\u0645\u0633\u0627\u0628\u0642\u0627\u062a-\u0648\u0631\u0632\u0634\u06cc-\u0628\u0647-\u0645\u062f\u062a-\u0631\u0648\u0632 |title=\u0644\u063a\u0648 \u0647\u0645\u0647 \u0645\u0633\u0627\u0628\u0642\u0627\u062a \u0648\u0631\u0632\u0634\u06cc \u0628\u0647 \u0645\u062f\u062a \u06f1\u06f0 \u0631\u0648\u0632|website=varzesh3.com|language=Persian|access-date=23 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nIran's Supreme Leader [[Ali Khamenei]] decided to cancel his [[Nowruz|Persian New Year]] speech which took place every year at the [[Imam Reza shrine]], [[Mashhad]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/09/Iran-s-Khamenei-cancels-Persian-new-year-speech-over-coronavirus-fears.html |title=Iran's Khamenei cancels Persian new year speech over coronavirus fears |work=[[Al Arabiya English]] |date=9 March 2020 |access-date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315075815/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/09/Iran-s-Khamenei-cancels-Persian-new-year-speech-over-coronavirus-fears.html |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> \n\nOn 22 February 2020, the [[Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance|Ministry of Islamic Culture and Guidance]], announced the cancellation of all concerts and other cultural events for one week.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iranian-doctors-call-for-long-holiday-to-contain-coronavirus-outbreak/30449047.html|title=Iranian Doctors Call For 'Long Holiday' To Contain Coronavirus, As Sixth Victim Dies|website=RFE/RL|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223130155/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iranian-doctors-call-for-long-holiday-to-contain-coronavirus-outbreak/30449047.html|archive-date=23 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>Traditional Persian fire festival [[Chaharshanbe Suri]] were also banned by the government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/iran-bans-fire-festival-celebrations-over-virus/1769048|title=Iran bans fire festival celebrations over virus|website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook India]]|access-date=20 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317180228/https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/iran-bans-fire-festival-celebrations-over-virus/1769048|archive-date=17 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> \n\nOn the last days of March,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.irna.ir/news/83727330/%D8%A8%D9%88%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%87%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D8%AC%D9%86%DA%AF%D9%84%DB%8C-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D8%AA%D8%B1%D8%AF%D8%AF-%D8%AA%D9%87%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%87-%D8%B4%D8%AF |title=The crowded parks were closed |publisher= IRNA|access-date= }}</ref> all parks and public gardens were closed by the order of officials and police didn't let people enter.<ref name= bbcmarch>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-52118809 |title=Coronavirus: Iran's official death toll passes 3,000 |publisher=BBC |access-date=1 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403142153/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-52118809 |archive-date=3 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n====Education====\nThe [[Ministry of Health and Medical Education]] also announced the closure of universities, higher educational institutions and schools in several cities and provinces.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-announces-closure-of-universities-schools-to-fight-coronavirus/30449711.html|title=Iran Announces Closure Of Universities, Schools As Coronavirus Death Toll Rises|website=RFE/RL|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223170351/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/iran-announces-closure-of-universities-schools-to-fight-coronavirus/30449711.html|archive-date=23 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Corona National Anti-Virus Headquarters ordered the academic organizations to launch [[learning management systems]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.ilna.news/\u0628\u062e\u0634-\u0627\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0646-\u0647\u0627-15/880494-\u0631\u0627\u0647-\u0627\u0646\u062f\u0627\u0632\u06cc-\u06a9\u0645\u067e\u06cc\u0646-\u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634-\u0647\u0627\u06cc-\u0645\u062c\u0627\u0632\u06cc-\u0631\u0627\u06cc\u06af\u0627\u0646-\u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc-\u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647-\u0628\u0627-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 |title= \u0631\u0627\u0647\u200c\u0627\u0646\u062f\u0627\u0632\u06cc \u06a9\u0645\u067e\u06cc\u0646 \u0622\u0645\u0648\u0632\u0634\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u062c\u0627\u0632\u06cc \u0631\u0627\u06cc\u06af\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0627 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 |accessdate= 3 March 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200315113600/https://www.ilna.news/%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%B4-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%87%D8%A7-15/880494-%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C-%DA%A9%D9%85%D9%BE%DB%8C%D9%86-%D8%A2%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B2%D8%B4-%D9%87%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%85%D8%AC%D8%A7%D8%B2%DB%8C-%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C%DA%AF%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%84%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7 |archive-date= 15 March 2020 |url-status= live }}</ref> Iran's health minister announced schools and universities closed until the start of the holiday for Persian new year [[Nowruz]] on 20 March 2020.<ref NAME=BBC52020/>\n\n====Religion====\nNevertheless, Iran's Health Ministry said that Friday prayers will not be held in Tehran and areas affected by the outbreak that week.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/saudi-arabia-halts-travel-to-islams-holiest-site-over-virus%2f2020%2f02%2f26%2fc86ec712-5918-11ea-8efd-0f904bdd8057_story.html |title=Iran news agencies report Friday prayers canceled in Tehran |first=Jon |last=Gambrell |agency=Associated Press |work=The Washington Post |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227215249/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/middle_east/saudi-arabia-halts-travel-to-islams-holiest-site-over-virus/2020/02/26/c86ec712-5918-11ea-8efd-0f904bdd8057_story.html |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 20 February, according to a letter of Iran's health ministry to the governor of Qom, a request was made to \"limit the number of pilgrims at the [[Fatima Masumeh Shrine]] and other religious sites\".<ref name=\"nyt\">{{cite news |title='Recipe for a Massive Viral Outbreak': Iran Emerges as a Worldwide Threat |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/24/world/middleeast/coronavirus-iran.html |website=NYT |accessdate=24 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312121420/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/02/24/world/middleeast/coronavirus-iran.html |archive-date=12 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> However, [[Shia]] shrines in Qom remained open for pilgrims to congregate.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/02/26/middleeast/iran-coronavirus-intl/index.html|title=Iran was already struggling with one crisis. Now it has the worst coronavirus outbreak in the Middle East|author1=Ramin Mostaghim|author2=Mostafa Salem|author3=Tamara Qiblawi|publisher=CNN|date=26 February 2020|access-date=26 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226200703/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/02/26/middleeast/iran-coronavirus-intl/index.html|archive-date=26 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> The head of Fatima Masumeh shrine encouraged pilgrims to visit the shrine on 27 February: \"We consider this holy shrine to be a place of healing.\"<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20200227-iran-cleric-encourages-visitors-to-qom-religious-sites-despite-coronavirus-fears/ |title=Iran cleric encourages visitors to Qom religious sites, despite coronavirus fears |date=27 February 2020 |work=Middle East Monitor |access-date=3 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303165907/https://www.middleeastmonitor.com/20200227-iran-cleric-encourages-visitors-to-qom-religious-sites-despite-coronavirus-fears/ |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March 2020, to prevent the spread of coronavirus, Fatima Masumeh Shrine, Jamkaran Mosque in Qom, and Imam Reza Shrine in Mashhad were closed.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/covid-19-irans-holiest-sites-closing-to-visitors/1768192l|title=COVID-19: Iran's holiest sites closing to visitors|website=AA news|access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref> Following this announcement, some people protested to enter the shrine but they were driven out of the shrine by servants and the doors were closed again.<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.farsnews.ir/qom/news/13981226001206/\u0648\u0631\u0648\u062f-\u063a\u06cc\u0631\u0642\u0627\u0646\u0648\u0646\u06cc-\u0639\u062f\u0647%E2%80%8C\u0627\u06cc-\u0628\u0647-\u062d\u0631\u0645-\u062d\u0636\u0631\u062a-\u0645\u0639\u0635\u0648\u0645\u0647-\u0633--\u0628\u0627-\u062a\u0644\u0627\u0634-\u062e\u062f\u0627\u0645-\u062f\u0631\u0628%E2%80%8C\u0647\u0627\u06cc-\u062d\u0631\u0645 |title=\u0648\u0631\u0648\u062f \u063a\u06cc\u0631\u0642\u0627\u0646\u0648\u0646\u06cc \u0639\u062f\u0647\u200c\u0627\u06cc \u0628\u0647 \u062d\u0631\u0645 \u062d\u0636\u0631\u062a \u0645\u0639\u0635\u0648\u0645\u0647 (\u0633)|website=Fars news|access-date=16 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://time.com/5804546/iran-shiite-storm-coronavirus/ |title=Shiite Hardliners in Iran Storm 2 Shrines That Were Closed to Stop Coronavirus Spread |first=Jon |last=GambrellA |agency=Associated Press |date=17 March 2020 |work=Time |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317140841/https://time.com/5804546/iran-shiite-storm-coronavirus/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n====Travels ====\nPresident [[Hassan Rouhani]] ordered the [[Ministry of Roads and Urban Development]] to make decisions about public commuting and the [[Ministry of Industry, Mine and Trade]] to build the required medical equipment.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.saat24.news/news/484027/\u0631\u0648\u062d\u0627\u0646\u06cc-\u062f\u0633\u062a\u0648\u0631\u0627\u062a-\u0644\u0627\u0632\u0645-\u0631\u0627-\u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc-\u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647-\u0647\u0645\u0647-\u062c\u0627\u0646\u0628\u0647-\u0628\u0627-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627-\u0635\u0627\u062f\u0631|title=\u0631\u0648\u062d\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u062f\u0633\u062a\u0648\u0631\u0627\u062a \u0644\u0627\u0632\u0645 \u0631\u0627 \u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647 \u0647\u0645\u0647\u200c\u062c\u0627\u0646\u0628\u0647 \u0628\u0627 \"\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627\" \u0635\u0627\u062f\u0631 \u06a9\u0631\u062f|date=23 February 2020|website=\u0633\u0627\u0639\u062a24|language=fa|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223183241/https://www.saat24.news/news/484027/%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B2%D9%85-%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%84%D9%87-%D9%87%D9%85%D9%87-%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%B1|archive-date=23 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>As confirmed cases mounted, Iran's health minister announced on 5 March 2020 that checkpoints would be placed between cities to limit travel.<ref name=BBC52020/>The government has indicated that it may use force to limit travel between cities.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/06/chinese-schools-reopen-as-coronavirus-cases-in-europe-continue-to-rise |title=Iran threatens use of force to restrict spread of coronavirus |author1=Sam Jones |author2=Patrick Wintour |date=6 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200306123813/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/06/chinese-schools-reopen-as-coronavirus-cases-in-europe-continue-to-rise |archive-date=6 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 17 March the government warned that \"millions\" might die from the coronavirus if people keep ignoring health guidelines and continue traveling. 90% of the 18,000 coronavirus cases in the Middle East have taken place in Iran; 988 people have died in the country.<ref>{{cite web|agency=Associated Press|title=Iran warns virus could kill 'millions' in Islamic Republic|author1=NASSER KARIMI|author2=JON GAMBRELL|date=17 March 2020|url=https://apnews.com/6e92d93551ee6c6ae51d0acaaad9eb32|access-date=17 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318132446/https://apnews.com/6e92d93551ee6c6ae51d0acaaad9eb32|archive-date=18 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus pandemic 'could kill millions' in Iran |publisher=Al Jazeera |date=16 May 2020 |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/coronavirus-pandemic-kill-millions-iran-200317135500255.html |access-date=17 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317222216/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/coronavirus-pandemic-kill-millions-iran-200317135500255.html |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 20 March, Media reports suggested that heavy traffic continued for the Nowruz holiday. A government minister had warned that the crisis might continue for six months if the disease is not brought under control.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/20/iranian-new-year-self-isolate-covid-19 |title=Iranians ignore requests to stay home for new year celebrations |first=Patrick |last=Wintour |date=20 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |access-date=27 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327150524/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/20/iranian-new-year-self-isolate-covid-19 |archive-date=27 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 25 March 2020, the government warned that Iran may be facing a second wave of coronavirus outbreak because people were ignoring guidance on travelling during the Nowruz holidays, and banned all new trips between cities.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-wave/iran-warns-of-second-wave-of-coronavirus-idUSKBN21C1VT |title=Iran warns of second wave of coronavirus |date=25 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |first= Parisa|last= Hafezi}}</ref>\n\n===Economic decision ===\n[[Administrative and Recruitment Affairs Organization]] ruled that [[telecommuting]] of government employees would be permissible.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.asriran.com/fa/news/716947/\u0628\u062e\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647%E2%80%8C-\u0628\u0647-\u062f\u0633\u062a\u06af\u0627\u0647-\u0647\u0627\u06cc-\u0627\u062c\u0631\u0627\u06cc\u06cc-\u062f\u0648\u0631\u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06cc-\u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06a9\u0646\u0627\u0646-\u0628\u0644\u0627\u0645\u0627\u0646\u0639-\u0627\u0633\u062a |title= \u0628\u062e\u0634\u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647\u200c \u0628\u0647 \u062f\u0633\u062a\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0627\u062c\u0631\u0627\u06cc\u06cc: \u062f\u0648\u0631\u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06cc \u06a9\u0627\u0631\u06a9\u0646\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0644\u0627\u0645\u0627\u0646\u0639 \u0627\u0633\u062a |accessdate= 3 March 2020 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20200304160526/https://www.asriran.com/fa/news/716947/%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%B4%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%87%E2%80%8C-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%AF%D8%B3%D8%AA%DA%AF%D8%A7%D9%87-%D9%87%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D8%A7%D8%AC%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C%DB%8C-%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%DA%A9%D8%A7%D8%B1%DB%8C-%DA%A9%D8%A7%D8%B1%DA%A9%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D8%B3%D8%AA |archive-date= 4 March 2020 |url-status= live }}</ref> On 24 March, President Rouhani announced that half of all government employees would work remotely at home.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-health-coronavirus-iran/half-of-iranian-government-employees-to-work-remotely-amid-coronavirus-rouhani-idUKKBN21B0SZ |title=Half of Iranian government employees to work remotely amid coronavirus \u2013 Rouhani |date=24 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |access-date=28 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328135328/https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-health-coronavirus-iran/half-of-iranian-government-employees-to-work-remotely-amid-coronavirus-rouhani-idUKKBN21B0SZ |archive-date=28 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>In order to restrict the spread of the disease, closing most businesses deemed non-essential has been performed.<ref name=\"timesofisrael2020\">{{cite web |last1=AFP |title=Iran says coronavirus infections show \u2018gradual\u2019 decline |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/iran-says-coronavirus-infections-show-gradual-decline/ |website=timesofisrael |accessdate=6 April 2020}}</ref>According to Rouhani, \"the authorities had given the go-ahead for the resumption of certain economic activities \u201cstep by step\u201d from April 11\".<ref name=\"timesofisrael2020\"/>\n\nOn 26 March 2020 President Rouhani made a request to withdraw 1&nbsp;billion dollars from [[National Development Fund of Iran|National Development Fund]] and Supreme leader Khamenei has allowed to withdrawal after eleven days. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/persian/iran-52189469|title=\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627\u061b \u0622\u06cc\u062a\u200c\u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u062e\u0627\u0645\u0646\u0647\u200c\u0627\u06cc \u067e\u0633 \u0627\u0632 \u06f1\u06f1 \u0631\u0648\u0632 \u0628\u0627 \u0628\u0631\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a \u0627\u0632 \u0635\u0646\u062f\u0648\u0642 \u062a\u0648\u0633\u0639\u0647 \u0645\u0644\u06cc \u0645\u0648\u0627\u0641\u0642\u062a \u06a9\u0631\u062f|first=|last=|website=bbc|access-date=7 March 2020}}</ref>On 28 March 2020, President Rouhani announced that 20% of the country's annual budget would be allocated to fight the virus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.tasnimnews.com/en/news/2020/03/28/2232142/iran-allocates-20-of-annual-budget-to-coronavirus-battle |title=Iran Allocates 20% of Annual Budget to Coronavirus Battle |agency=Tasnim News Agency |date=28 March 2020 |access-date=28 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200328112109/https://www.tasnimnews.com/en/news/2020/03/28/2232142/iran-allocates-20-of-annual-budget-to-coronavirus-battle |archive-date=28 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> The following day, he defended against criticisms of the government's response to the outbreak, saying that he needed to weigh protecting the country economy that was already affected by US sanctions while fighting the worst outbreak of the region.<ref name=\"aljazeera29032020\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jamaran.news/\u0628\u062e\u0634-\u067e\u0631\u0648\u0641\u0627\u06cc\u0644-182/1363201-\u0627\u062e\u062a\u0635\u0627\u0635-\u0645\u06cc\u0644\u06cc\u0627\u0631\u062f-\u062a\u0648\u0645\u0627\u0646-\u0628\u0647-\u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a-\u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a-\u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc-\u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647-\u0628\u0627-\u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627|title=\u0627\u062e\u062a\u0635\u0627\u0635 530 \u0645\u06cc\u0644\u06cc\u0627\u0631\u062f \u062a\u0648\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0647 \u0648\u0632\u0627\u0631\u062a \u0628\u0647\u062f\u0627\u0634\u062a \u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc \u0645\u0642\u0627\u0628\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0627 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627|website=\u067e\u0627\u06cc\u06af\u0627\u0647 \u062e\u0628\u0631\u06cc \u062c\u0645\u0627\u0631\u0627\u0646 \u2013 \u0627\u0645\u0627\u0645 \u062e\u0645\u06cc\u0646\u06cc \u2013 \u0627\u0646\u0642\u0644\u0627\u0628 \u0627\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645\u06cc|language=fa|access-date=23 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315091035/https://www.jamaran.news/%D8%A8%D8%AE%D8%B4-%D9%BE%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%81%D8%A7%DB%8C%D9%84-182/1363201-%D8%A7%D8%AE%D8%AA%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%B5-%D9%85%DB%8C%D9%84%DB%8C%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AF-%D8%AA%D9%88%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%88%D8%B2%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D9%87%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B4%D8%AA-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%DB%8C-%D9%85%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%84%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%DA%A9%D8%B1%D9%88%D9%86%D8%A7|archive-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Infected Iranian officials==\n*February\nDr. Iraj Harirchi tested positive for SARS-CoV-2 infection.<ref name=\"MEE_MOHME_deputy_min_positive\">{{cite news |title=Iran's deputy health minister tests positive for coronavirus |date=25 February 2020 |newspaper=[[Middle East Eye]] |url= https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/irans-deputy-health-minister-tests-positive-coronavirus |accessdate=25 February 2020 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20200225130856/https://www.middleeasteye.net/news/irans-deputy-health-minister-tests-positive-coronavirus |archivedate= 25 February 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>Mahmoud Sadeghi, an MP from Tehran, also tested positive for the virus.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51628484 |title=Top Iran health official gets virus as fears grow |date=25 February 2020 |work=BBC News |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303072933/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51628484 |archive-date=3 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Ebtekar\">{{cite web |url=http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/27/Iranian-Vice-President-Masoumeh-Ebtekar-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-Report.html |title=Iranian Vice President Masoumeh Ebtekar tests positive for coronavirus: Report |publisher=Al Arabiya |date=26 February 2020  |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227135129/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/02/27/Iranian-Vice-President-Masoumeh-Ebtekar-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-Report.html |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Iran's Vice President of Iran for Women and Family Affairs, [[Masoumeh Ebtekar]], was diagnosed with COVID-19, as well as the Chairman of the Iranian Parliament's National Security and Foreign Affairs Committee, [[Mojtaba Zonnour|Mojtaba Zolnour]].<ref name=\"Ebtekar\" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/high-ranking-iranian-official-catches-coronavirus/1746752 |title=High-ranking Iranian official catches coronavirus |website=aa.com.tr |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227161444/https://www.aa.com.tr/en/health/high-ranking-iranian-official-catches-coronavirus/1746752 |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/coronavirus-iran-vice-president-masoumeh-ebtekar-test-positive-outbreak-latest-a9363181.html |title=Iran's vice-president diagnosed with coronavirus |date=27 February 2020 |website=The Independent  |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227151952/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/coronavirus-iran-vice-president-masoumeh-ebtekar-test-positive-outbreak-latest-a9363181.html |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Iran's First Ambassador to the Vatican, [[Hadi Khosroshahi]], died from COVID-19 infection in Qom.<ref name=\"Ebtekar\" />\n*March\n[[Mohammad Mirmohammadi]], a member of the Expediency Council which advises the [[Supreme Leader of Iran|Supreme Leader]] [[Ali Khamenei]], was reported to have died of the disease.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://time.com/5793379/iran-supreme-leader-adviser-coronavirus/ |title=Adviser to Iranian Supreme Leader Khamenei Dies of Coronavirus |author1=Nasser Karimi |author2=Jon Gambrell |date=2 March 2020 |work=Time |access-date=2 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302154723/https://time.com/5793379/iran-supreme-leader-adviser-coronavirus/ |archive-date=2 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>23 members of the [[Islamic Consultative Assembly|Iranian Parliament]] were reported to have been infected.<ref name=henley /> The head of emergency medical services, Pirhossein Kolivand, was diagnosed with the disease.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/coronavirus-iran-emergency-medical-services-pirhossein-kolivand-a9371991.html|title=Coronavirus: Iran's head of emergency medical services diagnosed with disease|first=Rory|last=Sullivan|work=The Independent|date=3 March 2020|access-date=3 March 2020|archive-url