, and parliament was indefinitely suspended.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/another-senior-iranian-politician-has-died-of-coronavirus-2020-3?r=US&IR=T |title=Another senior politician has died of coronavirus in Iran, where 8% of the parliament is infected |work=Business Insider |first=David |last=Choi |date=5 March 2020 |access-date=6 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310050641/https://www.businessinsider.com/another-senior-iranian-politician-has-died-of-coronavirus-2020-3?r=US&IR=T |archive-date=10 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Elected Member of Parliament [[Fatemeh Rahbar]] died due to coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/iranian-mp-dies-from-coronavirus-tasnim-news-agency-idUSKBN20U0DL |title=Iranian MP dies from coronavirus: Tasnim news agency |date=7 March 2020 |accessdate=7 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200307154240/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran/iranian-mp-dies-from-coronavirus-tasnim-news-agency-idUSKBN20U0DL |archive-date=7 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Ayatollah {{ill|Reza Mohammadi Langroudi|fa|\u0631\u0636\u0627 \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f\u06cc \u0644\u0646\u06af\u0631\u0648\u062f\u06cc}} also died from the virus.<ref name=\"Langroudi\">{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/07/Two-Iranian-religious-figures-latest-to-die-of-coronavirus-in-Iran.html |title=Two Iranian religious figures latest to die of coronavirus in Iran |date=7 March 2020 |accessdate=7 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Arabiya English]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315075740/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/07/Two-Iranian-religious-figures-latest-to-die-of-coronavirus-in-Iran.html |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> {{ill|Esmail Najjar|fa|\u0627\u0633\u0645\u0627\u0639\u06cc\u0644 \u0646\u062c\u0627\u0631}}, the chief of Iran's Crisis Management Organization, was infected with coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.radiofarda.com/a/chief-of-iran-s-crisis-management-quarantined-due-to-coronavirus/30477355.html |title=Chief Of Iran's Crisis Management Quarantined Due To Coronavirus |date=9 March 2020 |accessdate=9 March 2020 |publisher=[[Radio Farda]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310050655/https://en.radiofarda.com/a/chief-of-iran-s-crisis-management-quarantined-due-to-coronavirus/30477355.html |archive-date=10 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Former MP [[Mohammad-Reza Rahchamani]] died from the virus.<ref name=\"Rahchamani\">{{cite news|title=Former Iranian MP dies of coronavirus|url=https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/445916/Former-Iranian-MP-dies-of-coronavirus|date=9 March 2020|accessdate=9 March 2020|newspaper=[[Tehran Times]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310050701/https://www.tehrantimes.com/news/445916/Former-Iranian-MP-dies-of-coronavirus|archive-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Farhad Tazari, the former head of the Islamic Revolution Guards Corps\u2019 Political Bureau, also died of coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://ifpnews.com/coronavirus-kills-two-more-iranian-politicians|title=Coronavirus Kills Two More Iranian Politicians|work=IFP News|date=9 March 2020|access-date=10 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200310152232/https://ifpnews.com/coronavirus-kills-two-more-iranian-politicians|archive-date=10 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>Iran's First Vice President [[Eshaq Jahangiri]] was infected with the virus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://news-tunisia.tunisienumerique.com/coronavirus-irans-first-vice-president-jahangiri-infected/ |title=Coronavirus: Iran's first vice president Jahangiri infected |date=11 March 2020 |accessdate=11 March 2020 |publisher=Tunisie Numerique |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312060842/https://news-tunisia.tunisienumerique.com/coronavirus-irans-first-vice-president-jahangiri-infected/ |archive-date=12 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Other two sick officials were [[Ali Asghar Mounesan]], minister of cultural heritage, handicrafts and tourism, and [[Reza Rahmani]], minister of industry, mines and business.<ref name=\"iran-vice-president-ministers-stricken-coronavirus\">{{cite news |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-vice-president-ministers-stricken-coronavirus-200311155806337.html |title=Iran's vice president and two ministers stricken by coronavirus |date=11 March 2020 |accessdate=11 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Jazeera]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200311194200/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/03/iran-vice-president-ministers-stricken-coronavirus-200311155806337.html |archive-date=11 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/iran-vice-president-2-cabinet-members-reportedly-diagnosed-with-coronavirus/ |title=Iran vice president, 2 cabinet members reportedly diagnosed with coronavirus |date=11 March 2020 |accessdate=11 March 2020 |magazine=[[Times of Israel]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312131059/https://www.timesofisrael.com/iran-vice-president-2-cabinet-members-reportedly-diagnosed-with-coronavirus/ |archive-date=12 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>Member of [[Expediency Discernment Council]] [[Ali Akbar Velayati]] was infected with the virus.<ref name=\"velayati\">{{cite news |title=Top adviser to Iran's supreme leader infected with coronavirus: Tasnim |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-aide/top-adviser-to-irans-supreme-leader-infected-with-coronavirus-tasnim-idUSKBN20Z38J |accessdate=12 March 2020 |agency=Reuters |date=12 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200313002146/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-iran-aide/top-adviser-to-irans-supreme-leader-infected-with-coronavirus-tasnim-idUSKBN20Z38J |archive-date=13 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>[[Nasser Shabani]], a senior commander of [[Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps]] (IRGC), has died from the virus.<ref name=\"shabani-dies\">{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/13/Senior-Iranian-IRGC-commander-dies-of-coronavirus-.html |title=Senior Iranian IRGC commander dies of coronavirus |date=13 March 2020 |accessdate=13 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Arabiya English]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314172342/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/13/Senior-Iranian-IRGC-commander-dies-of-coronavirus-.html |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>[[Minoo Mohraz]], a member of committee to combat Coronavirus, tested positive for the virus.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/14/Iran-Member-of-committee-to-combat-Coronavirus-tests-positive-for-the-virus.html |title=Iran: Member of committee to combat Coronavirus tests positive for the virus |date=14 March 2020 |accessdate=14 March 2020 |publisher=[[Al Arabiya English]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316012227/http://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/14/Iran-Member-of-committee-to-combat-Coronavirus-tests-positive-for-the-virus.html |archive-date=16 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>[[Hashem Bathaie Golpayegani]] and economist [[Fariborz Raisdana]] died from the virus.<ref name=\"golpayegani-dies\">{{cite news |title=Top Iranian cleric among those tasked with choosing supreme leader succumbs to coronavirus infection |url=https://www.rt.com/news/483203-iran-top-cleric-coronavirus/ |accessdate=16 March 2020 |agency=RT News |date=16 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317040733/https://www.rt.com/news/483203-iran-top-cleric-coronavirus/ |archive-date=17 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Iran Assembly of Experts member infected with coronavirus |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/15/Iran-Assembly-of-Experts-member-infected-with-coronavirus.html |accessdate=15 March 2020 |agency=Al Arabiya English |date=15 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315113238/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/15/Iran-Assembly-of-Experts-member-infected-with-coronavirus.html |archive-date=15 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.asriran.com/fa/news/718963|title=\u0641\u0631\u06cc\u0628\u0631\u0632 \u0631\u0626\u06cc\u0633 \u062f\u0627\u0646\u0627\u060c \u0627\u0642\u062a\u0635\u0627\u062f\u062f\u0627\u0646\u060c \u0628\u0631 \u0627\u062b\u0631 \u0627\u0628\u062a\u0644\u0627 \u0628\u0647 \u06a9\u0631\u0648\u0646\u0627 \u062f\u0631\u06af\u0630\u0634\u062a|publisher=Asr Iran|date=16 March 2020|accessdate=16 March 2020}}</ref>Former MP [[Hamid Kahram]] died from the coronavirus.<ref name=\"kahram-dies\">{{cite news |title=Former Iran MP Hamid Kahram dies from coronavirus |url=https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/20/Former-Iran-MP-Hamid-Kahram-dies-from-coronavirus.html |accessdate=20 March 2020 |agency=Al Arabiya English |date=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320025009/https://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/middle-east/2020/03/20/Former-Iran-MP-Hamid-Kahram-dies-from-coronavirus.html |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==International spread ==\n{{Further|Travel restrictions related to the 2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic}}\n[[Image:Imported COVID-19 Cases from Iran.svg|thumb|250px|World countries with [[COVID-19]] cases linked to Iranian [[Disease cluster|clusters]]]]\n\nOn 20 February, a SARS-CoV-2 confirmed case was reported for a woman in her 30s who had arrived in Canada from Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bc.ctvnews.ca/b-c-s-new-coronavirus-case-is-woman-who-recently-returned-from-iran-1.4821112|title=B.C.'s new coronavirus case is woman who recently returned from Iran|last=Holliday|first=Ian|date=20 February 2020|website=British Columbia|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221134501/https://bc.ctvnews.ca/b-c-s-new-coronavirus-case-is-woman-who-recently-returned-from-iran-1.4821112|archive-date=21 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 25 February, a woman in her 60s, and the next day her husband, who was also in his 60s, tested positive for SARS-CoV-2.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cp24.com/news/toronto-husband-of-ontario-s-fifth-covid-19-case-test-positive-for-virus-1.4829825|title=Toronto husband of Ontario's fifth COVID-19 case test positive for virus|last=Herhalt|first=Chris|website=cp24|date=27 February 2020|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227133459/https://www.cp24.com/news/toronto-husband-of-ontario-s-fifth-covid-19-case-test-positive-for-virus-1.4829825|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>On 21 February, [[Lebanon]] confirmed the first COVID-19 case, a 45-year-old woman travelling from [[Qom]], [[Iran]] was admitted to a hospital in [[Beirut]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://arab.news/9byac|title=Lebanon confirms first coronavirus case as death toll hits 4 in Iran|date=21 February 2020|website=Arab News|access-date=21 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://time.com/5789360/iran-coronavirus-death-toll/|title=Iran COVID-19 Death Toll Reaches 8, With 43 Confirmed Infection Cases|date=23 February 2020|website=Time|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225145921/https://time.com/5789360/iran-coronavirus-death-toll/|archive-date=25 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> On 24 February, Neighbouring countries Kuwait, Iraq and [[Bahrain]] announced that it recorded their first coronavirus cases from people who came from Iran.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-gulf-idUSKCN20I0PB|title=Kuwait, Bahrain, Iraq report coronavirus cases linked to Iran|date=24 February 2020|agency=Reuters|access-date=24 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200224143132/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-gulf-idUSKCN20I0PB|archive-date=24 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> According to the report of Oman's Health Ministry, there are two Omani women who visited Iran and now infected with the coronavirus.<ref Name= oman/>On 26 February, [[Pakistan]] announced two persons had been diagnosed with COVID-19, one of them known to have visited Iran.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200226-pakistan-confirms-first-two-cases-of-coronavirus|title=Pakistan confirms first two cases of coronavirus|date=26 February 2020|publisher=France 24|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226203500/https://www.france24.com/en/20200226-pakistan-confirms-first-two-cases-of-coronavirus|archive-date=26 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] confirmed the first COVID-19 case, a 50-year-old Georgian man who returned from Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://civil.ge/archives/340246|title=Georgia Confirms First Case of Coronavirus|date=26 February 2020|website=Civil.ge|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227050210/https://civil.ge/archives/340246|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> China confirmed a man in [[Zhongwei]], Ningxia, who returned from Iran, tested positive for SARS-CoV-2.<ref>{{cite web |author1=\u65b0\u4eac\u62a5 |title=\u5b81\u590f\u53d1\u73b01\u4f8b\u5883\u5916\u8f93\u5165\u578b\u65b0\u51a0\u80ba\u708e\u75c5\u4f8b \u6025\u5bfb\u5bc6\u5207\u63a5\u89e6\u8005 |url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/02/26/695546.html |language=zh |access-date=1 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200226131611/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/news/2020/02/26/695546.html |archive-date=26 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Estonia confirmed the first COVID-19 case, an Iranian citizen living in [[Estonia]] who returned from Iran.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://news.err.ee/1057196/first-coronavirus-case-found-in-estonia |title=First Coronavirus case found in Estonia |date=27 February 2020 |publisher=ERR News |location=Estonia |access-date=27 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227065704/https://news.err.ee/1057196/first-coronavirus-case-found-in-estonia |archive-date=27 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Kuwait]] confirmed 43 cases of COVID-19, all of them involved people who had travelled to Iran in February.<ref>{{cite news|author=Sara Al Shurafa|url=https://gulfnews.com/world/gulf/kuwait/kuwait-confirms-43-cases-of-coronavirus-all-coming-from-iran-1.1582789585309|title=Kuwait confirms 43 cases of coronavirus, all coming from Iran|date=27 February 2020|work=Gulf News|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227105047/https://gulfnews.com/world/gulf/kuwait/kuwait-confirms-43-cases-of-coronavirus-all-coming-from-iran-1.1582789585309|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Germany, [[Norway]], Sweden and Spain also confirmed new cases involving individuals with previous travels to Iran.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.trust.org/item/20200227142333-5k62k/|title=Lebanon health ministry confirms third case of coronavirus, NNA reports|last=Foundation|first=Thomson Reuters|website=news.trust.org|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227153900/https://news.trust.org/item/20200227142333-5k62k/|archive-date=27 February 2020|url-status=live}}\n*{{cite web|url=https://www.swr.de/swraktuell/rheinland-pfalz/kaiserslautern/Neuer-Fall-in-Rheinland-Pfalz-Coronavirus-bei-Patienten-in-Kaiserslautern-festgestellt,corona-kaiserslautern-100.html|title=Coronavirus bei Patient in Kaiserslautern festgestellt|last=Aktuell|first=S. W. R.|last2=Aktuell|first2=S. W. R.|website=swr.online|language=de|access-date=27 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200227170424/https://www.swr.de/swraktuell/rheinland-pfalz/kaiserslautern/Neuer-Fall-in-Rheinland-Pfalz-Coronav